Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setCompressLevel(25.10)                                setCompressLevel(25.10)

Name
       setCompressLevel  -  Specifies  the  compression level to use when com-
       pressing large data files

Syntax
       setCompressLevel <value>

       Specifies the compression level to  use  when  compressing  large  data
       files.  A  higher compression level creates a more compressed file, but
       at the cost of speed. A lower compression level  creates  a  less  com-
       pressed  file, but speeds up the process. By default, the software uses
       the gzip default value, that is 6, which results in high compression at
       the cost of speed.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setCompressLevel parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setCompressLevel

       <value>
              Specifies the compression level to use when compressing files.

              You can specify -1 or values between 1 and 9, where:

              1 Creates the least compressed files at the highest speed.

              9 Creates the most compressed files at the lowest speed.

              -1 Returns to the gzip default value, that is 6  (Z_DEFAULT_COM-
              PRESSION).

              Data_type: int, required

Examples
              * The  following  command sets the highest compression level and
                results in the most compressed data:

                setCompressLevel 9

              * The following command resets the compression level to the gzip
                default, that is 6.

                setCompressLevel -1

